The paper discusses algorithms for colour segmentation, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The use of a physical approach and region adjacency graph framework suggests that the paper is likely to be in the computer vision (cs.CV) or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The use of image models and pre-processing techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
